{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EVMzhHc8WZZB1gM4GYnKms","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Self-Evolution System Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4→\n     5→**Goal:** Implement a daemon-side post-run evolution pipeline that analyzes workflow history to automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows.\n     6→\n     7→**Architecture:** Multi-stage LLM pipeline (Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor branches) running in the daemon after each workflow completion. Three executor branches: Prompt Curator (ACE-style), Script Generator (LLM code gen), DSL Mutator (deterministic Go). Changes auto-applied with JSONL audit trail and snapshots.\n     8→\n     9→**Tech Stack:** Go, SQLite, gRPC, TOML config (`github.com/BurntSushi/toml`), existing LLM agent invocation pattern.\n    10→\n    11→**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→## Task 1: Extend Domain Types\n    16→\n    17→**Files:**\n    18→- Modify: `internal/domain/run.go`\n    19→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n    20→- Test: `internal/domain/run_test.go`\n    21→\n    22→**Step 1: Write failing test for Run.ProjectDir**\n    23→\n    24→Add to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:\n    25→\n    26→```go\n    27→func TestRunProjectDir(t *testing.T) {\n    28→\tr := NewRun(\"test-1\", \"develop\")\n    29→\tr.ProjectDir = \"/home/user/project\"\n    30→\tassert.Equal(t, \"/home/user/project\", r.ProjectDir)\n    31→}\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n    35→\n    36→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n    37→Expected: FAIL — `r.ProjectDir undefined`\n    38→\n    39→**Step 3: Add ProjectDir to Run**\n    40→\n    41→In `internal/domain/run.go`, add `ProjectDir string` to the `Run` struct.\n    42→\n    43→**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n    44→\n    45→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n    46→Expected: PASS\n    47→\n    48→**Step 5: Write failing test for StepExecution new fields**\n    49→\n    50→Add to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:\n    51→\n    52→```go\n    53→func TestStepExecutionCapturedData(t *testing.T) {\n    54→\texec := &StepExecution{\n    55→\t\tStepName:      \"implement\",\n    56→\t\tPromptText:    \"Write a hello world\",\n    57→\t\tAgentOutput:   \"Here is the code...\",\n    58→\t\tAttemptNumber: 2,\n    59→\t}\n    60→\tassert.Equal(t, \"Write a hello world\", exec.PromptText)\n    61→\tassert.Equal(t, \"Here is the code...\", exec.AgentOutput)\n    62→\tassert.Equal(t, 2, exec.AttemptNumber)\n    63→}\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→**Step 6: Run test to verify it fails**\n    67→\n    68→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestStepExecutionCapturedData -v`\n    69→Expected: FAIL — fields undefined\n    70→\n    71→**Step 7: Add fields to StepExecution**\n    72→\n    73→In `internal/domain/run.go`, add to `StepExecution`:\n    74→```go\n    75→PromptText    string\n    76→AgentOutput   string\n    77→AttemptNumber int\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→**Step 8: Run all domain tests**\n    81→\n    82→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -v`\n    83→Expected: ALL PASS\n    84→\n    85→**Step 9: Commit**\n    86→\n    87→```bash\n    88→git add internal/domain/\n    89→git commit -m \"feat(domain): add ProjectDir to Run, capture fields to StepExecution\"\n    90→```\n    91→\n    92→---\n    93→\n    94→## Task 2: SQLite Schema Migration\n    95→\n    96→**Files:**\n    97→- Modify: `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n    98→- Test: `internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`\n    99→\n   100→The current `migrate()` function uses `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`. We need to add\n   101→columns to existing tables and a new `evolution_log` table. Use `ALTER TABLE` with\n   102→error suppression (SQLite returns error if column already exists — catch and ignore).\n   103→\n   104→**Step 1: Write failing test for project_dir persistence**\n   105→\n   106→Add to `internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`:\n   107→\n   108→```go\n   109→func TestRunProjectDir(t *testing.T) {\n   110→\tstore, err := NewStore(\":memory:\")\n   111→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   112→\n   113→\trun := domain.NewRun(\"test-1\", \"develop\")\n   114→\trun.ProjectDir = \"/home/user/project\"\n   115→\trun.Start()\n   116→\n   117→\terr = store.CreateRun(context.Background(), run)\n   118→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   119→\n   120→\tgot, err := store.GetRun(context.Background(), \"test-1\")\n   121→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   122→\tassert.Equal(t, \"/home/user/project\", got.ProjectDir)\n   123→}\n   124→```\n   125→\n   126→**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n   127→\n   128→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/sqlite/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n   129→Expected: FAIL — column doesn't exist or field not scanned\n   130→\n   131→**Step 3: Update schema and CRUD methods**\n   132→\n   133→In `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`:\n   134→\n   135→1. In `migrate()`, after existing `CREATE TABLE` statements, add:\n   136→```go\n   137→// Schema evolution - add columns (ignore errors if already exist)\n   138→alterStatements := []string{\n   139→    `ALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''`,\n   140→    `ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN prompt_text TEXT`,\n   141→    `ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN agent_output TEXT`,\n   142→    `ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN attempt_number INTEGER DEFAULT 0`,\n   143→}\n   144→for _, stmt := range alterStatements {\n   145→    db.Exec(stmt) // ignore \"duplicate column\" errors\n   146→}\n   147→\n   148→// New tables\n   149→db.Exec(`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS evolution_log (\n   150→    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   151→    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL,\n   152→    workflow_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n   153→    trigger_run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n   154→    created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n   155→    classification TEXT,\n   156→    changes_json TEXT NOT NULL,\n   157→    knowledge_delta TEXT\n   158→)`)\n   159→```\n   160→\n   161→2. Update `CreateRun` to include `project_dir` in INSERT\n   162→3. Update `GetRun` to scan `project_dir`\n   163→4. Update `ListRuns` to scan `project_dir`\n   164→5. Update `SaveCapture` to include `prompt_text`, `agent_output`, `attempt_number`\n   165→6. Update `GetCaptures` to scan the new fields\n   166→\n   167→**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n   168→\n   169→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/sqlite/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n   170→Expected: PASS\n   171→\n   172→**Step 5: Write test for captured data round-trip**\n   173→\n   174→Add to `internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`:\n   175→\n   176→```go\n   177→func TestCaptureWithPromptAndOutput(t *testing.T) {\n   178→\tstore, err := NewStore(\":memory:\")\n   179→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   180→\n   181→\trun := domain.NewRun(\"test-1\", \"develop\")\n   182→\trun.Start()\n   183→\tstore.CreateRun(context.Background(), run)\n   184→\n   185→\texec := &domain.StepExecution{\n   186→\t\tStepName:      \"implement\",\n   187→\t\tPromptText:    \"Write hello world\",\n   188→\t\tAgentOutput:   \"Here is the code\",\n   189→\t\tAttemptNumber: 1,\n   190→\t\tStartedAt:     time.Now(),\n   191→\t}\n   192→\terr = store.SaveCapture(context.Background(), \"test-1\", exec)\n   193→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   194→\n   195→\tcaps, err := store.GetCaptures(context.Background(), \"test-1\")\n   196→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   197→\trequire.Len(t, caps, 1)\n   198→\tassert.Equal(t, \"Write hello world\", caps[0].PromptText)\n   199→\tassert.Equal(t, \"Here is the code\", caps[0].AgentOutput)\n   200→\tassert.Equal(t, 1, caps[0].AttemptNumber)\n   201→}\n   202→```\n   203→\n   204→**Step 6: Run test**\n   205→\n   206→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/sqlite/ -run TestCaptureWithPromptAndOutput -v`\n   207→Expected: PASS (if step 3 was done correctly)\n   208→\n   209→**Step 7: Run all store tests**\n   210→\n   211→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/sqlite/ -v`\n   212→Expected: ALL PASS\n   213→\n   214→**Step 8: Commit**\n   215→\n   216→```bash\n   217→git add internal/adapters/sqlite/\n   218→git commit -m \"feat(sqlite): add project_dir, prompt capture, and evolution_log schema\"\n   219→```\n   220→\n   221→---\n   222→\n   223→## Task 3: Evolution Store Port and Implementation\n   224→\n   225→**Files:**\n   226→- Modify: `internal/ports/store.go`\n   227→- Modify: `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n   228→- Test: `internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`\n   229→\n   230→**Step 1: Define EvolutionStore interface**\n   231→\n   232→Add to `internal/ports/store.go`:\n   233→\n   234→```go\n   235→type EvolutionEntry struct {\n   236→\tID             string\n   237→\tProjectDir     string\n   238→\tWorkflowName   string\n   239→\tTriggerRunID   string\n   240→\tCreatedAt      time.Time\n   241→\tClassification string\n   242→\tChangesJSON    string\n   243→\tKnowledgeDelta string\n   244→}\n   245→\n   246→type EvolutionStore interface {\n   247→\tSaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n   248→\tGetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n   249→\tListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n   250→}\n   251→```\n   252→\n   253→**Step 2: Write failing test for ListRunsSince**\n   254→\n   255→Add to `internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`:\n   256→\n   257→```go\n   258→func TestListRunsSince(t *testing.T) {\n   259→\tstore, err := NewStore(\":memory:\")\n   260→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   261→\tctx := context.Background()\n   262→\n   263→\t// Create 3 runs for the same project+workflow\n   264→\tfor i, id := range []string{\"run-1\", \"run-2\", \"run-3\"} {\n   265→\t\tr := domain.NewRun(id, \"develop\")\n   266→\t\tr.ProjectDir = \"/project\"\n   267→\t\tr.Start()\n   268→\t\tr.StartedAt = time.Now().Add(time.Duration(i) * time.Minute)\n   269→\t\trequire.NoError(t, store.CreateRun(ctx, r))\n   270→\t}\n   271→\n   272→\t// List runs since run-1 (should return run-2 and run-3)\n   273→\truns, err := store.ListRunsSince(ctx, \"/project\", \"develop\", \"run-1\")\n   274→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   275→\tassert.Len(t, runs, 2)\n   276→}\n   277→```\n   278→\n   279→**Step 3: Run test to verify it fails**\n   280→\n   281→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/sqlite/ -run TestListRunsSince -v`\n   282→Expected: FAIL — method not found\n   283→\n   284→**Step 4: Implement EvolutionStore on SQLite Store**\n   285→\n   286→In `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`, add methods:\n   287→\n   288→- `SaveEvolution` — INSERT into `evolution_log`\n   289→- `GetLastEvolution` — SELECT from `evolution_log` WHERE project_dir AND workflow_name ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 1\n   290→- `ListRunsSince` — SELECT from `runs` WHERE project_dir AND workflow_name AND started_at > (SELECT started_at FROM runs WHERE id = sinceRunID). If sinceRunID is empty, return all runs for this project+workflow.\n   291→\n   292→**Step 5: Run tests**\n   293→\n   294→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/sqlite/ -v`\n   295→Expected: ALL PASS\n   296→\n   297→**Step 6: Commit**\n   298→\n   299→```bash\n   300→git add internal/ports/store.go internal/adapters/sqlite/"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kj2ES3fjZGEh5kyGTHhvDA","session_id":"e576fc45-fcda-491a-aa5c-2d5791efc9e9","uuid":"49889ae7-d901-4bbd-8f69-2e7870d2e716"}
