{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TKASY1CezdSvpWHNLhT1xt","type":"tool_result","content":"  1194→## Task 13: Script Generator (Branch B)\n  1195→\n  1196→**Files:**\n  1197→- Create: `internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n  1198→- Create: `internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`\n  1199→\n  1200→**Step 1: Write failing test**\n  1201→\n  1202→Create `internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`:\n  1203→\n  1204→```go\n  1205→package evolution\n  1206→\n  1207→import (\n  1208→\t\"context\"\n  1209→\t\"os\"\n  1210→\t\"path/filepath\"\n  1211→\t\"testing\"\n  1212→\n  1213→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n  1214→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n  1215→)\n  1216→\n  1217→func TestScriptGeneratorCreatesScript(t *testing.T) {\n  1218→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n  1219→\tos.MkdirAll(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\"), 0755)\n  1220→\n  1221→\tllm := &fakeLLM{response: `{\"path\": \"scripts/security-scan.sh\", \"content\": \"#!/bin/bash\\ngosec ./...\"}`}\n  1222→\tg := &ScriptGenerator{LLM: llm}\n  1223→\n  1224→\tlesson := &Lesson{\n  1225→\t\tID:              \"lesson-001\",\n  1226→\t\tCategory:        \"new_step\",\n  1227→\t\tStepType:        \"script\",\n  1228→\t\tSuggestedAction: \"Add gosec security scan\",\n  1229→\t}\n  1230→\n  1231→\tresult, err := g.Generate(context.Background(), dir, lesson)\n  1232→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1233→\tassert.Equal(t, \"scripts/security-scan.sh\", result.Path)\n  1234→\n  1235→\tcontent, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\", \"security-scan.sh\"))\n  1236→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1237→\tassert.Contains(t, string(content), \"gosec\")\n  1238→\n  1239→\t// Verify executable\n  1240→\tinfo, _ := os.Stat(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\", \"security-scan.sh\"))\n  1241→\tassert.NotZero(t, info.Mode()&0111)\n  1242→}\n  1243→```\n  1244→\n  1245→**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n  1246→\n  1247→Run: `go test ./internal/evolution/ -run TestScriptGenerator -v`\n  1248→Expected: FAIL — ScriptGenerator undefined\n  1249→\n  1250→**Step 3: Implement ScriptGenerator**\n  1251→\n  1252→Create `internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`:\n  1253→\n  1254→The ScriptGenerator:\n  1255→1. Sends the lesson to the LLM asking it to generate a checker script\n  1256→2. Parses the response as JSON with `path` and `content` fields\n  1257→3. Creates parent directories if needed\n  1258→4. Writes the script file with executable permissions (0755)\n  1259→5. For agent-type steps, generates a prompt file instead\n  1260→\n  1261→**Step 4: Run tests**\n  1262→\n  1263→Run: `go test ./internal/evolution/ -run TestScriptGenerator -v`\n  1264→Expected: ALL PASS\n  1265→\n  1266→**Step 5: Commit**\n  1267→\n  1268→```bash\n  1269→git add internal/evolution/\n  1270→git commit -m \"feat(evolution): add Script Generator for new checker steps\"\n  1271→```\n  1272→\n  1273→---\n  1274→\n  1275→## Task 14: DSL Mutator (Branch C)\n  1276→\n  1277→**Files:**\n  1278→- Create: `internal/dsl/mutator.go`\n  1279→- Create: `internal/dsl/mutator_test.go`\n  1280→\n  1281→This is the deterministic Go code that adds steps, wiring, and collect conditions\n  1282→to `.cloche` workflow files. Uses text-level manipulation (regex-based insertion at\n  1283→known structural positions) rather than a full round-trip AST, to keep scope manageable.\n  1284→Comments are preserved because we insert at boundaries rather than rewriting.\n  1285→\n  1286→**Step 1: Write failing test for AddStep**\n  1287→\n  1288→Create `internal/dsl/mutator_test.go`:\n  1289→\n  1290→```go\n  1291→package dsl\n  1292→\n  1293→import (\n  1294→\t\"testing\"\n  1295→\n  1296→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n  1297→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n  1298→)\n  1299→\n  1300→func TestMutatorAddStep(t *testing.T) {\n  1301→\tinput := `workflow develop {\n  1302→  step test {\n  1303→    run = \"make test\"\n  1304→    results = [success, fail]\n  1305→  }\n  1306→\n  1307→  test:success -> done\n  1308→  test:fail -> abort\n  1309→}`\n  1310→\n  1311→\tm := &Mutator{}\n  1312→\tresult, err := m.AddStep(input, StepDef{\n  1313→\t\tName:    \"security-scan\",\n  1314→\t\tType:    \"script\",\n  1315→\t\tConfig:  map[string]string{\"run\": `\"gosec ./...\"`},\n  1316→\t\tResults: []string{\"success\", \"fail\"},\n  1317→\t})\n  1318→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1319→\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"step security-scan\")\n  1320→\tassert.Contains(t, result, `run = \"gosec ./...\"`)\n  1321→\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"results = [success, fail]\")\n  1322→\n  1323→\t// Verify the result still parses\n  1324→\twf, err := Parse(result)\n  1325→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1326→\tassert.Contains(t, wf.Steps, \"security-scan\")\n  1327→}\n  1328→```\n  1329→\n  1330→**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n  1331→\n  1332→Run: `go test ./internal/dsl/ -run TestMutatorAddStep -v`\n  1333→Expected: FAIL — Mutator undefined\n  1334→\n  1335→**Step 3: Implement AddStep**\n  1336→\n  1337→Create `internal/dsl/mutator.go`:\n  1338→\n  1339→```go\n  1340→package dsl\n  1341→\n  1342→import (\n  1343→\t\"fmt\"\n  1344→\t\"regexp\"\n  1345→\t\"strings\"\n  1346→)\n  1347→\n  1348→type StepDef struct {\n  1349→\tName    string\n  1350→\tType    string // \"script\" or \"agent\"\n  1351→\tConfig  map[string]string\n  1352→\tResults []string\n  1353→}\n  1354→\n  1355→type WireDef struct {\n  1356→\tFrom   string\n  1357→\tResult string\n  1358→\tTo     string\n  1359→}\n  1360→\n  1361→type CollectAddition struct {\n  1362→\tCollectTarget string\n  1363→\tStep          string\n  1364→\tResult        string\n  1365→}\n  1366→\n  1367→type Mutator struct{}\n  1368→```\n  1369→\n  1370→The `AddStep` method:\n  1371→1. Finds the last `step ... { ... }` block in the file (regex for closing brace\n  1372→   pattern)\n  1373→2. Inserts the new step definition after it\n  1374→3. Serializes the step as DSL text with proper indentation\n  1375→4. Validates the result by calling `Parse()`\n  1376→\n  1377→**Step 4: Write failing test for AddWiring**\n  1378→\n  1379→```go\n  1380→func TestMutatorAddWiring(t *testing.T) {\n  1381→\tinput := `workflow develop {\n  1382→  step test {\n  1383→    run = \"make test\"\n  1384→    results = [success, fail]\n  1385→  }\n  1386→\n  1387→  step scan {\n  1388→    run = \"gosec ./...\"\n  1389→    results = [success, fail]\n  1390→  }\n  1391→\n  1392→  test:success -> done\n  1393→  test:fail -> abort"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kj2ES3fjZGEh5kyGTHhvDA","session_id":"e576fc45-fcda-491a-aa5c-2d5791efc9e9","uuid":"257434ba-2153-49ee-86ee-26a50d33c1bd"}
