{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J1bJyUbUgoyVUZTm65mJC3","type":"tool_result","content":"  1194→## Task 13: Script Generator (Branch B)\n  1195→\n  1196→**Files:**\n  1197→- Create: `internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n  1198→- Create: `internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`\n  1199→\n  1200→**Step 1: Write failing test**\n  1201→\n  1202→Create `internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`:\n  1203→\n  1204→```go\n  1205→package evolution\n  1206→\n  1207→import (\n  1208→\t\"context\"\n  1209→\t\"os\"\n  1210→\t\"path/filepath\"\n  1211→\t\"testing\"\n  1212→\n  1213→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n  1214→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n  1215→)\n  1216→\n  1217→func TestScriptGeneratorCreatesScript(t *testing.T) {\n  1218→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n  1219→\tos.MkdirAll(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\"), 0755)\n  1220→\n  1221→\tllm := &fakeLLM{response: `{\"path\": \"scripts/security-scan.sh\", \"content\": \"#!/bin/bash\\ngosec ./...\"}`}\n  1222→\tg := &ScriptGenerator{LLM: llm}\n  1223→\n  1224→\tlesson := &Lesson{\n  1225→\t\tID:              \"lesson-001\",\n  1226→\t\tCategory:        \"new_step\",\n  1227→\t\tStepType:        \"script\",\n  1228→\t\tSuggestedAction: \"Add gosec security scan\",\n  1229→\t}\n  1230→\n  1231→\tresult, err := g.Generate(context.Background(), dir, lesson)\n  1232→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1233→\tassert.Equal(t, \"scripts/security-scan.sh\", result.Path)\n  1234→\n  1235→\tcontent, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\", \"security-scan.sh\"))\n  1236→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1237→\tassert.Contains(t, string(content), \"gosec\")\n  1238→\n  1239→\t// Verify executable\n  1240→\tinfo, _ := os.Stat(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\", \"security-scan.sh\"))\n  1241→\tassert.NotZero(t, info.Mode()&0111)\n  1242→}\n  1243→```\n  1244→\n  1245→**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n  1246→\n  1247→Run: `go test ./internal/evolution/ -run TestScriptGenerator -v`\n  1248→Expected: FAIL — ScriptGenerator undefined\n  1249→\n  1250→**Step 3: Implement ScriptGenerator**\n  1251→\n  1252→Create `internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`:\n  1253→\n  1254→The ScriptGenerator:\n  1255→1. Sends the lesson to the LLM asking it to generate a checker script\n  1256→2. Parses the response as JSON with `path` and `content` fields\n  1257→3. Creates parent directories if needed\n  1258→4. Writes the script file with executable permissions (0755)\n  1259→5. For agent-type steps, generates a prompt file instead\n  1260→\n  1261→**Step 4: Run tests**\n  1262→\n  1263→Run: `go test ./internal/evolution/ -run TestScriptGenerator -v`\n  1264→Expected: ALL PASS\n  1265→\n  1266→**Step 5: Commit**\n  1267→\n  1268→```bash\n  1269→git add internal/evolution/\n  1270→git commit -m \"feat(evolution): add Script Generator for new checker steps\"\n  1271→```\n  1272→\n  1273→---"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e576fc45-fcda-491a-aa5c-2d5791efc9e9","uuid":"f5a512f4-d632-489f-a572-63f007d16005","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md","content":"## Task 13: Script Generator (Branch B)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n- Create: `internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write failing test**\n\nCreate `internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage evolution\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n)\n\nfunc TestScriptGeneratorCreatesScript(t *testing.T) {\n\tdir := t.TempDir()\n\tos.MkdirAll(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\"), 0755)\n\n\tllm := &fakeLLM{response: `{\"path\": \"scripts/security-scan.sh\", \"content\": \"#!/bin/bash\\ngosec ./...\"}`}\n\tg := &ScriptGenerator{LLM: llm}\n\n\tlesson := &Lesson{\n\t\tID:              \"lesson-001\",\n\t\tCategory:        \"new_step\",\n\t\tStepType:        \"script\",\n\t\tSuggestedAction: \"Add gosec security scan\",\n\t}\n\n\tresult, err := g.Generate(context.Background(), dir, lesson)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"scripts/security-scan.sh\", result.Path)\n\n\tcontent, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\", \"security-scan.sh\"))\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Contains(t, string(content), \"gosec\")\n\n\t// Verify executable\n\tinfo, _ := os.Stat(filepath.Join(dir, \"scripts\", \"security-scan.sh\"))\n\tassert.NotZero(t, info.Mode()&0111)\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/evolution/ -run TestScriptGenerator -v`\nExpected: FAIL — ScriptGenerator undefined\n\n**Step 3: Implement ScriptGenerator**\n\nCreate `internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`:\n\nThe ScriptGenerator:\n1. Sends the lesson to the LLM asking it to generate a checker script\n2. Parses the response as JSON with `path` and `content` fields\n3. Creates parent directories if needed\n4. Writes the script file with executable permissions (0755)\n5. For agent-type steps, generates a prompt file instead\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/evolution/ -run TestScriptGenerator -v`\nExpected: ALL PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/evolution/\ngit commit -m \"feat(evolution): add Script Generator for new checker steps\"\n```\n\n---","numLines":80,"startLine":1194,"totalLines":2046}}}
