{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CQWahDr2fL2yaCD8g1b8Ka","type":"tool_result","content":"4-\n5-Cloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\n6:automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\n7-time. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\n8-completion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\n--\n222-- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n223-  bullet/rule\n224:- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n225-  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n226-- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n--\n302-Finds the matching `collect` clause and adds the new condition.\n303-\n304:**Validation gate:** After any mutation, the mutator calls\n305:`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\n306-rejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n307-\n--\n322-   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n323-3. **Knowledge base update** — appends the Reflector's lessons to\n324:   `knowledge/<workflow>.md`, runs deduplication/refinement\n325-\n326-## Knowledge Base Structure"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e576fc45-fcda-491a-aa5c-2d5791efc9e9","uuid":"6f9b6c39-e580-4603-8080-1cbf235cd243","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"4-\n5-Cloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\n6:automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\n7-time. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\n8-completion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\n--\n222-- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n223-  bullet/rule\n224:- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n225-  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n226-- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n--\n302-Finds the matching `collect` clause and adds the new condition.\n303-\n304:**Validation gate:** After any mutation, the mutator calls\n305:`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\n306-rejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n307-\n--\n322-   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n323-3. **Knowledge base update** — appends the Reflector's lessons to\n324:   `knowledge/<workflow>.md`, runs deduplication/refinement\n325-\n326-## Knowledge Base Structure","numLines":24}}
